{"TopicId":75657,"ForumId":39,"TopicTitle":"Orbital plane program","CreatedByName":"gilflo","CreatedById":62881,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-06-21T16:44:54Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"gilflo","CreatedById":62881,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-06-21T16:44:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI have been playing KSP for more than 1 year and it\u0027s my first try in the SPH. I design an atmospheric plane easy to fly, big range, the idea being to launch it with a rocket and with its fuel station so that i can land on an atmospheric planet and refuel from the ground after flight. The fuel station contains 14 tanks and should allowed 5 refueling.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ELaunch tries were done on Kerbin, here is the launcher for the refueling station and the Mirage\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=208206screenshot75.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/208206screenshot75.png\u0022 alt=\u0022208206screenshot75.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EFlying and refueling were satisfactory\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=899539screenshot33.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/899539screenshot33.png\u0022 alt=\u0022899539screenshot33.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHere is the Mirage \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=228518screenshot27.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/228518screenshot27.png\u0022 alt=\u0022228518screenshot27.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ERefueling station\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=140772screenshot30.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/140772screenshot30.png\u0022 alt=\u0022140772screenshot30.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThat was quite easy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ENext step was to design an orbital plane that would be able:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E-To take of and set up in orbit 70Km\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E-De-orbit and land everywhere on Kerbin, so landing would be at the lowest weight.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E-Be flyable and land at the maximum weight, the idea being to launch it with a rocket, send it to another planet with a refueling station, make different flights and take off to join an orbit to be transferred on a rocket.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESo it must be flyable at all weight, whatever is the consumption and balancing. That was the biggest challenge.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI tried a lot of designs and when it was flyable at the maximum weight it was not at the lowest, because with consumption the CG is going backward.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThen I tried to add winlglet or canard to a movable rail using utilities of the add-on from Magic smoke industry. That was not satisfactory.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEventually I add a swept wings on moving rails and the space plane is flyable up to the lowest weight by moving backward the swept wings!\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHere is the orbital plane, \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E- for atmospheric flights: 4 turbojet engines with a 150L tank each and 6 radial air intakes each for the upper engines and 5 for the lower ones \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E-for space flights 3 rockets Vesta VR1 with 3 FLT 800 fuel tanks (360L - 4,5T)\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=751302screenshot39.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/751302screenshot39.png\u0022 alt=\u0022751302screenshot39.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI made a take off, followed by a landing at the maximum weight and it is very stable, but you need to make a smooth touch and to brake smoothly.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E on take off 31T for a trial orbit around Kerbin, followed by deorbiting and a landing on an island\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=849631screenshot42.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/849631screenshot42.png\u0022 alt=\u0022849631screenshot42.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=656815screenshot45.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/656815screenshot45.png\u0022 alt=\u0022656815screenshot45.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003Ein the air\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=646269screenshot47.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/646269screenshot47.png\u0022 alt=\u0022646269screenshot47.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=975235screenshot48.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/975235screenshot48.png\u0022 alt=\u0022975235screenshot48.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E4600M: you can see the 2 outer swept wings in advanced position\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=229498screenshot49.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/229498screenshot49.png\u0022 alt=\u0022229498screenshot49.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBetween 25000m and 30000m I change on rockets\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=908757screenshot50.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/908757screenshot50.png\u0022 alt=\u0022908757screenshot50.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003Eview of the moving swept wings\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=251626screenshot52.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/251626screenshot52.png\u0022 alt=\u0022251626screenshot52.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESwept wings are now in back position, weight is down to 21T\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=687353screenshot53.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/687353screenshot53.png\u0022 alt=\u0022687353screenshot53.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDeorbiting calculation, we have not enough DV to reach the island, but we will do it by flying\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=543041screenshot61.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/543041screenshot61.png\u0022 alt=\u0022543041screenshot61.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAtmosphere entry\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=131196screenshot62.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/131196screenshot62.png\u0022 alt=\u0022131196screenshot62.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003Ein sight of the island, turbojet engines have been restarted.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=582365screenshot63.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/582365s